<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4227f9b9-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s211"><num value="211">§ 211.</num><heading> Allowance of deductions</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In computing taxable income under section 63, there shall be allowed as deductions the items specified in this part, subject to the exceptions provided in part IX (section 261 and following, relating to items not deductible).</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id4227f9ba-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/69">68A Stat. 69</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/95/30/tI/s102/b/3">Pub. L. 95–30, title I, § 102(b)(3)</ref>, <date date="1977-05-23">May 23, 1977</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/91/137">91 Stat. 137</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id4227f9bb-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id4227f9bc-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id4227f9bd-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1977—<ref href="/us/pl/95/30">Pub. L. 95–30</ref> substituted “section 63” for “section 63(a)”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id4227f9be-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="id4227f9bf-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 1977 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/95/30">Pub. L. 95–30</ref> applicable to taxable years beginning after <date date="1976-12-31">Dec. 31, 1976</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/95/30/s106/a">section 106(a) of Pub. L. 95–30</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t26/s1">section 1 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
